Yes, definitely.

00:07:37.720 --> 00:07:41.720
And so that's when I you actually pink fairy did big time.

00:07:41.720 --> 00:07:42.720
Yes.

00:07:43.720 --> 00:07:46.720
So after after 1999, what happens next?

00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:48.720
Tell us more about your carnival adventures.

00:07:48.760 --> 00:07:57.760
Well, after 99, the carnival, my my I had a life changing experience because I met in the carnival,

00:07:57.760 --> 00:08:00.760
which is a mix of, you know, Caribbean cultures.

00:08:00.760 --> 00:08:05.760
It mixes. It is truly a intercultural experience.

00:08:05.760 --> 00:08:10.760
I met the father of my children who's from St. Vincent.

00:08:10.760 --> 00:08:17.760
Some of the the people running the carnival, some of the people making the costumes and working

00:08:17.800 --> 00:08:19.800
alongside Swicker were there.

00:08:19.800 --> 00:08:26.800
So I actually had my became a mother as a consequence of the carnival.

00:08:26.800 --> 00:08:28.800
What does carnival mean to you?

00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:29.800
Motherhood.

00:08:29.800 --> 00:08:30.800
It's a good answer.

00:08:30.800 --> 00:08:31.800
It's a good answer.

00:08:31.800 --> 00:08:37.800
The way I see it is that really I was kind of a mother figure when I was meeting people in the carnival.

00:08:37.800 --> 00:08:42.800
So it's sort of almost led into my role as a mother.

00:08:42.840 --> 00:08:48.840
However, I did continue with the carnival and I brought my children along there.

00:08:48.840 --> 00:08:57.840
Even there was one carnival when Rose, my daughter, was a couple of months old and I had her in my,

00:08:57.840 --> 00:09:01.840
you know, my little papoose in during the carnival.

00:09:01.840 --> 00:09:03.840
So I just integrated life.

00:09:03.840 --> 00:09:05.840
I think that's the great thing about the carnival.

00:09:05.840 --> 00:09:10.840
It is very much an all inclusive family event.

00:09:10.880 --> 00:09:17.880
So it didn't disclude me because I was, which often happens when you're in the creative industries,

00:09:17.880 --> 00:09:22.880
is that it's very much not family or child friendly.

00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:25.880
So that was the great thing about it for me anyway.

00:09:25.880 --> 00:09:26.880
So I could continue.

00:09:26.880 --> 00:09:35.880
I didn't I didn't work in the carnival, but I always brought my children and they got involved in the culture of.

00:09:35.880 --> 00:09:37.880
Literally carnival babies.

00:09:37.880 --> 00:09:39.880
Yes, they were carnival babies.

00:09:39.920 --> 00:09:40.920
Which is lovely, yes.

00:09:40.920 --> 00:09:43.920
I think that's fantastic.

00:09:45.920 --> 00:09:49.920
Could you say a little bit about, so obviously, yeah, carnival is something we share.

00:09:49.920 --> 00:09:56.920
Perhaps a bit about your arts practice, because I associate you with lots of interesting, exciting and spiritual things.

00:09:56.920 --> 00:09:57.920
That's right, yes.

00:09:57.920 --> 00:09:59.920
For future generations.

00:09:59.920 --> 00:10:03.920
In fact, as I was thinking of what the carnival meant to me,

00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:08.920
I did think that there is a certain amount of spiritual elements of the carnival as well.

00:10:08.960 --> 00:10:18.960
Because I felt that the whole drumming aspect of it is is is can draw parallels with with quite shamanic work

00:10:18.960 --> 00:10:24.960
and especially the tradition of going through the streets and the night before the carnival.

00:10:24.960 --> 00:10:27.960
The juve, the poor man's carnival.

